This paper deals with the degrees of freedom of a MIMO relay channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses joint transceiver design and interference cancellation, which are relevant to networked communication (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of multiple antennas is a key aspect of the paper, which is also relevant to wireless communication (cs.CE) and multimedia systems (cs.MM).
